label: Genève, Bibliothèque de Genève, Ms. lat. 34

metadata.label: Title (English)
metadata.value: Book of Hours for use in the Abbey of St. Martin of Tours

metadata.label: Place of Origin (English)
metadata.value: workshop of the Abbey of St. Martin of Tours (France, Indre-et-Loire) (cf. F. Huot)

metadata.label: Date of Origin (English)
metadata.value: second half of the 15th century (cf. F. Huot)

metadata.label: Summary (English)
metadata.value: This manuscript from the second half of the 15th century is a book of hours for use in the Abbey of St. Martin of Tours. Six large miniatures remain, of which two pertain to the life of Christ, two are dedicated to the Annunciation, one to St. Joseph, and the last to St. Barbara. The calendar indicates the thirteen unlucky days (dies eger) of the year. With its old crimson velvet binding, its painted decorations and careful script, this manuscript had enriched the collection of the Petau family before it came to Geneva.

metadata.label: Persons
metadata.value: Librarian: Aubert, Hippolyte; Former possessor: Lullin, Ami; Former possessor: Petau, Alexandre; Former possessor: Petau, Paul
